# SuggaPlay Marketing Positioning

Before writing **any** user-facing copy, read:

1. `docs/market-positioning/SuggaPlay-Brand-Positioning.pdf` (source: `new brand.pdf`)
2. `docs/market-positioning/README.md`

## Brand descriptor (non-negotiable)

**Not a dating app.**

> A private members' club for modern relationships.

## Homepage copy (use verbatim where marked)

- **Headline:** Meet people who live life on their own terms.
- **Sub:** For beautiful connections, honest intentions and unforgettable chemistry.
- **Solution:** Built around honesty.
- **Membership:** One membership. Unlimited conversations. No credits. No tokens. No counting every message.

## Emotional tone

Luxury fashion campaign — Saint Laurent, Soho House, Jacquemus energy. Not corporate startup copy. Not LinkedIn.

Use *lust* where the brief does — it is honest, human, and on-brand.

## Do not use (retired copy)

- "Meet successful people who know what they want." (too corporate)
- "Premium dating platform" as primary identity
- "Dating app" as brand descriptor
- Pricing psychology / overselling (founding cap badges, etc.) on homepage
- Copy from the old Brand & Marketing Brief unless it also appears in `SuggaPlay-Brand-Positioning.pdf`

## When copy conflicts

`docs/market-positioning/SuggaPlay-Brand-Positioning.pdf` wins for **all marketing and homepage copy**.

Product bible wins for **features and business rules**. Design bible wins for **visual design**.
